 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://usatodayhss.com/2015/how-trevor-lawrence-nations-no-1-sophomore-football-recruit-survives-the-hype|title=How Trevor Lawrence, nation's No. 1 sophomore football recruit, survives the hype|last=Barnett|first=Josh|date=October 14, 2015|website=[[USA Today]]|publisher=[[Gannett]]|accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nLawrence has been regarded as one of the best high school quarterback prospects ever, where he was a five-star recruit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/college-football-recruiting/2017/5/9/15586904/trevor-lawrence-qb-clemson-2018-signee|title=Who is Clemson QB Trevor Lawrence?|last=Kirshner|first=Alex|date=September 8, 2018|website=[[SB Nation]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|accessdate=September 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://247sports.com/Article/247Sports-football-recruiting-Debating-Trevor-Lawrence-or-Justin-Fields-111838848|title=Trevor Lawrence or Justin Fields? Debating 2018's top battle|last=247Sports staff|date=December 6, 2017|website=[[247Sports.com]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://n.rivals.com/news/ask-farrell-is-trevor-lawrence-the-best-qb-prospect-of-rivals-era-|title=Ask Farrell: Is Trevor Lawrence the best QB prospect of Rivals era?|author=Farrell|first=Mike|last2=Gorney|first2=Adam|date=November 19, 2018|website=[[Rivals.com]]|accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://n.rivals.com/content/prospects/2018/trevor-lawrence-1731|title=Trevor Lawrence, 2018 Pro-style quarterback|date=December 15, 2016|website=[[Rivals.com]]|accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref> On December 16, 2016, Lawrence committed to [[Clemson University]] to play college football.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/college-sports/recruiting/football/story/_/id/18291751/clemson-tigers-land-trevor-lawrence-no-1-qb-recruit-2018|title=Clemson lands Trevor Lawrence, No. 1 QB recruit of 2018|last=Hamilton|first=Gerry|date=December 16, 2016|web